- **Output**: <Report Name> in the format below

#### Final Report Format

```markdown
# <Report Name>

## Summary
<1-3 sentence overview>

## <Tier 1 — e.g., MUST-FIX / Critical Findings / GO-NO-GO Verdict>
- <item> — <evidence reference>

## <Tier 2 — e.g., SHOULD-FIX / Recommendations>
- <item>

## <Tier 3 — e.g., FYI / Observations>
- <item>

## Contradictions (A-pattern only — surfaced verbatim, NOT mediated)
- <Role X said "...", Role Y said "..." — human decides>

## Coverage Map (B-pattern only)
- Slice 1: <covered by role X>
- Slice 2: <covered by role Y>
- Gaps: <slices nobody covered, if any>

## Unresolved Disputes (Debate-pattern — preserved from cross-exam, NOT mediated)
- <Claim by Role X> vs <Counter by Role Y> — <synthesizer's assessment + what user should verify>
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- All roles returned outputs matching their `## Output Schema` (no malformed responses).
- Final Report contains all mandatory tiers.
- <Pattern-specific check, e.g., "All A-pattern contradictions surfaced verbatim, none mediated by Leader" / "All C-pattern gates passed or explicit kick-back recorded" / "All Debate-pattern unresolved disputes preserved with cross-exam context, not silently dropped">.
- <Coverage check, e.g., "All B-pattern slices accounted for in the Coverage Map">.

